<HEADLINE> Malaria Claims 18 Lives In Zambia's Southern Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Malaria has claimed 18 lives in
Zambia's southern town of Livingstone, Health Minister Michael
Sata revealed today.
</P>
<P>
Sata told a press conference that the government had expressed
concern at the increasing number of malaria cases reported in
Livingstone, which is the tourist capital of the country.
</P>
<P>
Everything possible would be done to control the disease, he
pledged.
</P>
<P>
Malaria has killed more people than AIDS in Zambia and the
situation in the tourist capital would soon be under control,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of cholera cases admitted to the Lusaka
health center had stabilized slightly, he said.
</P>
<P>
Some 60 cholera cases have been reported to the center since
it broke out in the capital last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
