<HEADLINE> Japan Grants Zimbabwe 15 Dollars In Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government today
provided an aid grant worth 15 million U.S. Dollars to Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
About 10 million U.S. Dollars will be used to support
Zimbabwe's second phase of the economic structural adjustment
programme started this year.
</P>
<P>
The rest of the grant will be channeled to road maintenance.
</P>
<P>
The agreement to effect the aid was signed here today by
Japanese Ambassador to Zimbabwe Asao Tsukahara and Zimbabwe
Finance Senior Secretary Charles Kuwaza. 
</P>
</TEXT>
