<HEADLINE> Jordan Calls for Regional Comprehensive Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan, the
Regent, called here today for forging a comprehensive Middle East
security system involving all states in the region to charter its
political image.
</P>
<P>
The crown prince said the new security arrangement should
address all issues at stake in accordance with the letters of the
Madrid and Barcelona peace conferences and last week's summit of
peacemakers in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to leading Arab and Turkish intellectuals at a
meeting on Arab-Turkish relations here today, he asked
participants to discuss a comprehensive concept to rehabilitate
the Middle East within the approach envisaging such basic elements
as security, economic cooperation and human cultural dialogue.
</P>
<P>
The crown prince told delegates that he backed a proposal by
Turkey earlier this month to hold a regional summit on water
sharing as part of comprehensive security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
