<HEADLINE> Christopher Praises GCC's Role in Preserving Peace in Gulf Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 18 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Warren Christopher praised in a message to the Gulf Cooperation
Council (GCC) Secretary General today the GCC's role in preserving
peace and security in the Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait News Agency reported today that Christopher also praised
the GCC for its efforts in helping achieve a comprehensive, just
and lasting peace in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Christopher's message came as the outgoing GCC Secretary
General Sheikh Fahim al Qassimi is to finish his three-year-term
at the end of this month and Jamil al-Hojeilan, a veteran Saudi
diplomat will succeed Qassimi as the GCC secretary general.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Qatari Foreign Minister Sheikh Hamad
Bin Jassem al-Thani announced at the end of a two-day GCC foreign
ministers meeting in Saudi capital of Riyadh Sunday that his
country endorsed the appointment of Hojeilan as the new secretary
general of the GCC.
</P>
<P>
Qatar boycotted the final session of the GCC summit in Omani
capital of Muscat on December 6 to protested the appointment of
Hojeilan as the GCC's secretary general. Qatar had insisted that
it should be the turn of a Qatari to hold the post.
</P>
<P>
The GCC groups Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, the United Arab Emirates,
Bahrain, Oman and Qatar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
