<HEADLINE> Eritrea, Canadian Company Signs Mineral Prospecting Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Energy,
Mines and Water Resources of Eritrea has signed two agreements
with a Canadian company on mineral prospecting in Debub and
Semenawi Keyih Bahri regions, according to the latest issue of
weekly "Eritrea Profile".
</P>
<P>
The agreements which were signed last Friday provide for
prospecting activities in gold and silver.
</P>
<P>
Under the first agreement, the Rift Resources Limited of
Toronto will carry out mineral prospecting over 220 sq. km in
Debub region for a period of three years.
</P>
<P>
The second agreement authorizes the same company to undertake
prospecting activities in Semenawi Keyih Bahri region over 1,900
sq. km for one year.
</P>
<P>
Recently, the Eritrean ministry concluded similar agreements
with the mining companies of Ghana and the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
