<HEADLINE> Britain's Drug Seizures Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 18 (Xinhua) -- An all-high of 55.6 tons of drugs
worth an estimated 457.6 million pounds (695.6 million US dollars)
were seized in Britain last year, reported BBC TV this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Customs and Excise identified the growth in heroin seizures, up
80 percent to 117.5 kilograms, as particularly alarming, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Customs and Excise was quoted as saying that
the increase was "supplier-led" as heroin was being imported in to
Britain to create a market.
</P>
<P>
Politicians and law enforcement agencies have warned of the
growing threat posed by drug smuggling, the report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
