<HEADLINE> Three British Boys Arrested for Possessing Arms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A 14-year-old schoolboy, who was
thought to have been armed with two rifles and two handguns was
arrested by police in Buckinghamshire today, according to a BBC TV
report this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Robert Crawley stole a cache of 22 arms and ammunition from a
secure cabinet in a house on Buckinghamshire and then disappeared
last Friday. Police used a helicopter and dogs in the search for
him.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that a high-powered target rifle had been
recovered and a search for other weapons is continuing.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, two teenage schoolboys in county Antrim, Northern
Ireland have been detained by police as they had been spotted
stuffing a loaded shotgun in a school bag.
</P>
<P>
The two unnamed boys aged 14 and 15 respectively are being
questioned.
</P>
<P>
Last Wednesday a massacre, took place in a primary school in
Dunblance, central Scotland and 16 children aged four to six and
their woman teacher were brutally killed and another 12 children
and two teachers injured.
</P>
<P>
Now the whole country is still in grief and demands that
control of firearms be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that some three million illegal weapons are
circulating in Britain. 
</P>
