<HEADLINE> Japan Nips Oman in Olympic Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Japan overwhelmed Oman 4-1
in its second match of Group A at the Asian Zone qualifying soccer
tournament for the Atlanta Olympic Games on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese team, who played to a 1-1 draw with Iraq on
Saturday, now became the hot favorite to enter the second stage as
one of top two in Group A.
</P>
<P>
Japan opened the lead in the 18th minute from Masakiyo Maezono
with a penalty goal awarded after the advancing striker Shoji Jo
was brought down by an Omani defender.
</P>
<P>
Oman launched all-out attacks after conceding the goal and
managed to equalise the score by Adil Fayel Muknaini in the 33th
minute.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese took advantage again in just five minutes when
Maezono fired home with his second goal.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the Japanese eleven displayed dominance
throughout, with Jo scoring the third in the 50th minute and
Hidetoshi Nakata the fourth in the 67th.
</P>
<P>
Japan will play against the winless United Arab Emirates in its
last group match on Wednesday.  
</P>
