<HEADLINE> UK Job Prospects Show Weaker Signs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A slowdown in the rate of growth
in new jobs in Britain is predicted by Manpower, the independent
employment agency, in a report published today.
</P>
<P>
Although employment prospects are positive, the year-on-year
trend for the second quarter of this year is the worst for three
years, says Manpower.
</P>
<P>
Lilian Bennett, chairman of Manpower, says: "While the overall
outlook is still positive, the year-on-year slowdown is cause of
concern."
</P>
<P>
Flexibility of the workforce is now one of management's top
priorities, with the demand for temporary staff still growing, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The survey, covering more than 2,200 companies, shows 22
percent of employers plan to recruit more staff, while 13 percent
predict a fall in the number of jobs.
</P>
<P>
The nine percentage points difference compares with a balance
of 12 percent in favor of job creation a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, little more than one in 10 employers take any active
steps towards recruiting disabled people, says a report published
today by the Institute of Employment Studies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
