<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Change Oil Price Formula </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian state-owned oil
company Pertamina will change its crude oil price formula next
month.
</P>
<P>
The scheduled increase will probably between 10 and 20 US cents
per barrel, according to a report submitted by Pertamina's General
Affairs Director Baharuddin which was received here today.
</P>
<P>
According to Baharuddin, Pertamina had proposed the change of
the formula to the government, and hopefully the government will
approve the proposed change.
</P>
<P>
Baharuddin said that Pertamina currently calculates its monthly
crude prices on a formula giving a 50 percent weighting to crude
oil price assessment on the APPI (Asian petroleum price index).
The other half is based on spot prices.
</P>
<P>
Pertamina is considering reducing the influence of the APPI
price index. 
</P>
</TEXT>
