<HEADLINE> Surveillance and Control of Communicable Diseases in EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brussels, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission(EC) said
today it had proposed to the European Parliament and the Council
of Ministers the creation of a network for the epidemiological
Surveillance and control of communicable diseases in the European
Union.
</P>
<P>
According to the EC, the aim of this proposal is to improve the
prevention and control of a number of serious communicable
diseases which necessitate the introduction of special measures
for the protection of the population.
</P>
<P>
The EC's proposal seeks to create a legal framework for the
setting up of a system of close cooperation and effective
coordination between Member States on communicable disease
surveillance.
</P>
<P>
The system would function both routinely and in emergencies,
the EC said. 
</P>
