<HEADLINE> Prominent Pakistani Opposition Leader Released </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Sheikh Rashid Ahmed, a
prominent opposition leader in Pakistan, was released on bail
today after one and a half years in jail.
</P>
<P>
Rashid, member of the National Assembly and former Minister of
Industry in the Nawaz Sharif government, was received by thousands
of opposition activists.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme Court Sunday granted bail to the opposition
parliamentarian against a security deposit of 10,000 rupees (about
294 US dollars) in La Haveli case in which he was accused of
firing at the police.
</P>
<P>
Rashid was arrested by police in October 1994 on charges of
possessing a Russian made Kalashnikov rifle and firing during the
opposition's protest movement and was sentenced to seven years'
imprisonment by a special court for terrorists activities in
February 1995.
</P>
<P>
Rashid was acquitted by the Lahore High Court in the case of
unlicensed Kalashnikov last week after the government announced
not to contest the case.  
