<HEADLINE> Agricultural Development Bank to Issue Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Development Bank
(ADB) of China is expected to float ten billion yuan-worth of
financial bonds this year.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time for the bank to issue bonds since its
establishment in 1994, said ADB officials.
</P>
<P>
"Raising long-term funds on the financial market will improve
our debt structure, reduce our reliance on the central bank for
capital supply and pool more funds for agricultural investment,"
they added.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the State Development Bank of China is
expected to arrange 12.843 billion yuan in loans for 252 state key
projects within the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that by March 7 the bank had provided
6.572 billion yuan in loans, and another 5.757 billion will flow
into the targeted projects by March 20.
</P>
<P>
These loans will benefit such state key projects as the Three
Gorges Project, and the development of commodity grain production
bases, coalfields, railway lines, automobile factories,
water-control projects and fertilizer factories.
</P>
<P>
The bank has paid special attention to hydroelectric projects,
the construction of which is usually affected during the flood
season, in arranging loans this winter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
