<HEADLINE> Explosion Hits College in Central Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A fragmentation grenade lobbed by
an unidentified man exploded this morning inside a guardhouse in a
college in the central Philippines, seriously wounding two
security guards.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here, the suspect immediately
escaped aboard a taxi after he threw an apple-type grenade inside
a security outpost at the John P. Lacson college in the central
city of Bacolod, some 450 km south of Manila.
</P>
<P>
Police said the wounded sustained shrapnel wounds in different
parts of the bodies and were brought to a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
While conducting an investigation, police said the possible
terrorists' involvement in the explosion cannot be easily
dismissed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
