<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 15:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eight Killed in Nursing Home Fire in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A fire raged through a nursing
home in eastern U.S. overnight, killing at least eight residents
and injuring two others, fire officials said.
</P>
<P>
The fire with billowing smoke swept the men's wing of the
Scotch Meadow Rest Home at Laurinburg, North Carolina, late Sunday
night, but it was quickly contained and extinguished.
</P>
<P>
Fire doors separating the men's and women's sides closed
automatically and helped keep the fire from spreading, said Ron
Danella, owner of the 60-bed nursing home.
</P>
<P>
Fire officials said all the eight victims had been overcome by
heavy smoke. The two injured also suffered mainly from smoke
inhalation.
</P>
<P>
About 40 other residents at the nursing home, most of them aged
from 70 to 90, were evacuated to a nearby motel.
</P>
<P>
Danella said investigators told him the fire was caused by an
electrical fire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
