<HEADLINE> Champion Ma Beaten in Third Match of Pro Go Chess </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Ma Xiaochun of
China crashed out to Lee Changho of South Korea in the third game
of the best-of-five Pro Go Chess final here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Playing the balck, the Chinese nine-dan Ma failed to grasp a
good chance in the 151st move that led to his defeat.
</P>
<P>
Ma and seven-dan Lee shared the leading position with one win
and one loss in the first two mathes.
</P>
<P>
Lee now leads the final with 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Six players from China, Japan and South Korea, with each
country having two, were qualified for the annual go chess
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Ma and Lee will play their fourth encounter of the final on
Wendesday. 
