<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, today called for concerned government departments to
do a better job of rehabilitating the mausoleum of Emperor
Huangdi, located in northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark during a working meeting to mark the third
anniversary of the establishment of Mausoleum Foundation for
rehabilitating the massive tomb of the emperor.
</P>
<P>
Li is also honorary chairman of the foundation.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out at the meeting that the situation as regards the
mausoleum does not match the economic and social development level
China has achieved these days, saying that Huangdi was one of the
ancestors of the Chinese nation and forefathers of Chinese
civilization.
</P>
<P>
Through the rehabilitation of the mausoleum Chinese people both
at home and abroad can learn more about China's history and be
stimulated to make their contributions to the nation's
development, Li said. 
