<HEADLINE> HK Jewelry Show attracts big business orders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Total business orders saw
double-digit growth in value at this year's Hong Kong
International Jewelry Show, according to the leading organizer
Trade Development Council.
</P>
<P>
A total of 782.7 million HK dollars (100 million US dollars)
worth of business orders were placed at the four-day jewelry show
last week, a 44-percent rise over the results of 1995's fair.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 600 exhibitors from 25 countries and regions took part
in the gala, one of the most important annual jewelry trade events
in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The show saw a large number of buyers from the Middle East,
North America, Europe and other parts of Asia. Out of the 12,400
buyers, 5,000 came from overseas.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong hosted its first international jewelry
show in 1987. The show last week was the 13th. 
</P>
