<HEADLINE> Turkish Cypriot Leader Discharged from Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf
Denktash was discharged from hospital in Ankara this afternoon
and left for northern Cyprus by a private plane provided by
Turkish President Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
Denktash, 72, suffered a heart attack in northern Cyprus on
March 3 and was flown to Ibni Sina Hospital of Ankara University
for treatment on March 4.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided since 1974 when Turkey intervened
in the Mediterranean island following a short-lived coup by
Greek Cypriots seeking union with Greece.
</P>
<P>
In 1983, the Turkish Cypriots unilaterally declared a
breakaway state which was recognized only by Turkey. 
