<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Leading Group for Science, Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A national leading group for
China's science and technology with Chinese Premier Li Peng as the
head was set up here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the first meeting of the group, Li said that to make
a success of the Ninth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000) and the
long-term goal for the year 2010, China must rely on the progress
of science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The leading group will be mainly responsible for studying and
formulating national policies with regard to science and
technology, discussing and deciding on important science and
technology tasks and projects, and coordinating the science and
technology work between various government departments.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the leading group will help the enforcement of the
strategy of "reinvigorating the nation through science and education",
the macro-control and management of science and technology
work and the concentration of manpower, and material and financial
resources to promote the scientific progress of the whole society.
</P>
<P>
He commented positively on China's achievements in science and
technology during the Eighth Five-Year Plan period (1991-1995) and
stressed that the way out for the development of science and
technology in China will continue to lie in the deepening of the
reform.  
</P>
