<HEADLINE> China Science, Technology Hall Built in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Hall of Science and
Technology, with a total floor space of 56,000 sq m, was
completed today after more than a decade of construction.
</P>
<P>
The hall has realized a long-cherished dream of Chinese
scientists, said Zhuang Fenggan, vice-chairman of the Chinese
Association of Science and Technology, at the inauguration ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Located in the western part of the city, the 25-story building
can hold both domestic and international science and technology
activities as well as large conferences. It has a 600-seat
auditorium, a 300-seat studio and a multi-purpose hall with a floor
space of 1,000 sq m.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Guangzhao, president of the Chinese Academy of Sciences,
gave a report, titled "The Trend of Science and Technology and Its
Role in Society" after the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua and other senior officials who had
attended the ceremony listened to the report.
</P>
<P>
More reports on various topics of science and technology will
be given to government officials in Beijing, Shanghai, Tianjin and
nine other cities by over 100 members of the Chinese Academy of
Sciences and the Chinese Academy of Engineering.  
</P>
