<HEADLINE> China, US Join Hands to Explore for Offshore Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Offshore Oil
Corporation (CNOOC) and the Triton Energy Corp. of the US signed a
second contract here today to explore for oil in the 16/03 block
of the Pearl River Delta, about 150 km southeast of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Block 16/03 is about 8,900 sq km, with water depths ranging
from 100 to 200 m, according to the CNOOC.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract, Triton will undertake the seismic data
collection, information analysis and drilling of exploratory wells.
</P>
<P>
The Block is contiguous to Block 16/22, its second oil
contract with the CNOOC, which is surrounded by oil fields on two
sides. Geological studies show that the two blocks are promising,
for they are located on moving oil-and gas-bearing
structures.
</P>
<P>
Triton expects to begin drilling the first exploratory
well this April.
</P>
<P>
Triton is an independent oil and gas exploration company
primarily focussing on oil and gas exploration and
production. It has business operations in 17 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
