<HEADLINE> France, Poland Split Modern Pentathlon Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 18 (Xinhua) -- France staged an excellent
performance on the last day of the 14th Egyptian International
Modern Pentathlon Championships to win the team title Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Czyzowicz Maciey of Poland scored a total of 5,666
points from five events -- shooting, swimming, fencing, running
and horse riding -- to snatch the individual crown.
</P>
<P>
The French team, composed of Ibanez Olivier, Mailard Olivier
and Duran Fabrice, overcame a tough challenge from its Polish
counterpart to garner 3,110 points in horse riding for a total of
15,907 points.
</P>
