<HEADLINE> GE Sets Up 14th Joint Venture in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The General Electric Company (GE)
of the United States has set up a joint venture in Chengdu,
capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province, bringing the number
of GM-Chinese joint ventures to 14, with a total investment valued
at 150 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The company, named the GE Medical Systems (Xinan) Company,
between GE Medical Systems and China's Xinan Medical Equipment
Company, is also the second joint venture GE has established in
Sichuan.
</P>
<P>
The new company, with total investment of six million US
dollars, will develop, manufacture, install and service X-ray
equipment.
</P>
<P>
GE Xinan is also GE Medical Systems' second joint venture in
China. The first, GE Hang Wei Medical Systems (GEHW), was
established in 1991 here. A partnership between GE and the Beijing
Changfeng Group, GEHW manufactures Computed Tomography (CT)
scanners for domestic use and for export.
</P>
<P>
Besides direct investment, the GE Finance Company has poured into
China over one billion US dollars by way of aircraft and container
leasing.
</P>
<P>
In 1994 GE purchased from China products valued at 40 million
US dollars. It also employs over 8,000 Chinese nationals.  
</P>
