<HEADLINE> Swedish Prime Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Prime Minister Ingvar
Carlsson today officially offered his resignation to the Swedish
Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The Speaker of Parliament Birgitta Dahl demanded that
Carlsson, 61, stay in the cabinet as caretaker leader until the
new prime minister, Goran Persson, is officially sworn in later
this week.
</P>
<P>
Carlsson, who resigned as head of the ruling Social Democratic
Party (SDP) last Friday, became prime minister after the
assassination of his predecessor Olof Palme 10 years ago. He
announced last August that he would resign after 40 years in
public life.
</P>
<P>
Goran Persson, currently finance minister, was named
Carlsson's successor as party leader and prime minister by the SDP
last Friday. 
