<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 12:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Acting Macao Governor's Wife Reportedly Attacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MACAO, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Acting Macao Governor Henrique
Lages Ribeiro's wife and her friend were attacked by three
hooligans last night when they were leaving a Portuguese style
restaurant at about ten o'clock, local newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to a report in today's Macao Daily News, Ribeiro's
wife, Maria da Piedade, got bruised in the right cheek and a blow
in the belly when she tried to stop hooligans from beating her
friend. The friend was said to have been slapped on the face and
hurt seriously.
</P>
<P>
Both of them have been treated in local hospital.
</P>
<P>
Another report in the "Va Kio" newspaper said that two
suspects were detained early this morning. Police is making
further investigations into the case.
</P>
<P>
A local police officer was quoted by the paper as saying that
the attack was caused "by mistake". The culprits may have taken
her friend as someone else, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
Ribeiro, deputy secretary for security of the Macao
Government, becomes the acting governor when Governor Vasco Rocha
Vieira left for Lisbon for the inauguration of Portuguese new
president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
