<HEADLINE> Chinese Herbal Medicines Popular in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese Pharmaceuticals and
Herbal Medicines Import and Export Fair, held for the first time
in Macao from March 14 to 19, has witnessed a brisk business so
far, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Contracts worth more than 3 million US dollars of Chinese
herbal medicines were signed during the first three days of the
fair.
</P>
<P>
A total of 25 companies from China's 22 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions attended the fair,
displaying products ranging from ginseng, pilose antler, dangshen,
Chinese wolfberry fruit to other health-promotion products.
</P>
<P>
Businessmen from Hong Kong, Taiwan, Singapore, Japan and
Thailand as well as Macao attended the fair.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
