<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 12:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Jobless Rate Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in Hong
Kong edged down during the period between December 1995 and
February 1996, when more jobs were offered in such major sectors
as restaurants and hotels.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest figures released today by the Census
and Statistics Department, the seasonally adjusted jobless rate
was 3.1 percent and the underemployment rate was 2.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Both figures fell down from the period between November 1995
and January 1996, when the unemployment rate was 3.2 percent and
the underemployment rate was 2.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said that decreases in the jobless rate
were recorded in most major sectors, including restaurants and
hotels, transport, construction and manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
The labor force statistics were obtained from a continuous
General Household Survey, which covered 18,100 families or 61,400
persons selected to represent the population in the territory.
</P>
</TEXT>
