<HEADLINE> Champions Israel Fall at World Bowls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Champions Israel suffered a
surprise defeat to Australia at the triple matches on the opening
day of the world bowls championships in Adelaide, Australia, on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Australia's Ian Taylor, Kelvin Kerkow and Steve Anderson fought
back from a 7-1 deficit after five ends to upset the Israeli
combination of Leon Blum, Lawrence Mendelsohn and Jeffrey Rabkin
15-12 in Section A.
</P>
<P>
Blum and Mendelsohn were members of Israel's winning team at
Worthing, England, four years ago.
</P>
<P>
In other triples matches, Guernsey beat Kenya 20-11, the United
States downed Singapore 26-19, Ireland defeated Malaysia 21-11 and
Wales nipped Thailand 44-7.
</P>
<P>
In the pairs, Australians Cameron Curtis and Rex Johnston won
over outsider Botswana 22-18 in Section B.
</P>
<P>
Defending pairs champions Scotland's Richard Corsie and
Alexander Marshall beat South African opponents 21-20 in their
opening Section A match.
</P>
<P>
England overpowered Brazil 25-9 and Singapore edged out Zambia
19-17. 
</P>
