<HEADLINE> Uganda Conservative Party Elects New President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Uganda Conservative Party
(CP) has elected Hajji Nsubuga Nsambu as acting president of the
CP, a CP statement announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The statement said 25 members of the National Executive
Committee and 10 branch leaders as well as parliamentary
candidates meeting here Saturday relieved the party's National
Chairman Muyanja Nkangi for being unfaithful to the principles of
the party.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also abolished the post of party chairman.
</P>
<P>
It accused Nkangi of abandoning the federal cause of the party
in and outside the constituent assembly.
</P>
<P>
It stated that Nkangi, Minister of Finance and Economic
Planning, abandoned the federal principle and became a full
member of the National Resistance Movement, saying as a party
leader, therefore, he has no plan to steer the CP in the coming
elections.
</P>
<P>
The statement reaffirmed the party's resolve to join the
National Inter Party Cooperation (IPC) which comprises the
Democratic Party and the Uganda People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
It said a new and vigorous drive has started to reorganize the
party to fully participate in the forthcoming elections under the
IPC umbrella. 
</P>
</TEXT>
