<DOCNO> XIE19960318.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 12:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lao Party President Delivers Political Report  at Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENTIANE, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Khamtay Siphandone, president
of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party, said here today that
during the 1991-95 period, the gross domestic product of Laos
reached an annual average increase of 6.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed this in his political report delivered to the
three-day sixth congress of the party, which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
However, he said during the next five years up to the year
2000, the living standard and cultural level of the Laotian people
will rise, considering that the country has good land, rich
forest, water, mine ores, and tourism resources such as beautiful
scenery.
</P>
<P>
For the next five years (1996-2000), the party will strive to
ensure that the economy grows to the tune of 8-8.5 percent per
year. By 2000, per capita income must reach 500 US dollars (not
considering inflation), he said.
</P>
<P>
But he did not say how much it is now. It is widely believed
that per capita income now stands at 350 US Dollars. Land-locked
Laos is listed by the United Nations as one of the world's least
developed nations.
</P>
<P>
Khamtay also said that Laos must build a number of basic works
to serve as basis for the further industrialization and
modernization of the country.
</P>
<P>
He is also committed to solving food scarcity and poverty in
some priority areas in close connection with all-round rural
development.
</P>
<P>
On foreign affairs, he said Laos follows the policy of peace,
independence, friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In this regard, he said Laos' traditional friendly relations
and all-round cooperation with China have been expanded in terms
of scope and depth.
</P>
<P>
In years to come, Laos will develop the solidarity and
friendship, all-round cooperation and mutual support and
assistance with China.
</P>
<P>
Its relations with neighboring countries, such as Myanmar and
the member countries of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) have stepped up to a higher degree.
</P>
<P>
Laos will continue to prepare actively to become member of
ASEAN and actively participate in its activities with other member
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said Laos must open wider relations and cooperation with
various countries in the world, monetary institutions and
non-governmental organizations.
</P>
<P>
He said opening up of external economic relations and promotion
of foreign investment is a major policy of the party aimed at
tapping the international potentials to combine with domestic ones
for the development of the country.
</P>
<P>
In this aspect, Laos must prepare all conditions for membership
of ASEAN's Free Trade Area (AFTA) and the World Trade
Organizations (WTO), he concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
