<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three African Soccer Squads Qualify for Atlanta Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Ghana, Nigeria and Tunisia
split the three Atlanta Olympic berths for Africa in the
qualifying soccer tournament on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria edged Zimbabwe 1-0 in their final qualifying round,
second leg tie in Lagos on Sunday while Ghana drew and Tunisia
were beaten in their respective matches but both won through on
aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Dutch-based striker Tijani Babangida scored the only goal in
the first half before a crowd of 45,000 to ensure a 2-0 aggregate
win for Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia lost 2-0 to Guinea in Conakry but their first leg lead
was enough to secure them a place at the Atlanta Games in July.
</P>
<P>
Wandeh Soumah scored both goals but Tunisa won the
qualification since they took the first leg 5-2.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona Olympic bronze medalist Ghana were held to a goaless
draw by Cameroon in their second leg tie in Yaounde on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
But Ghana's 3-0 home win in Kumasi two weeks ago was enough to
ensure a comfortable aggregate triumph. 
</P>
</TEXT>
