<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 12:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Breweries Makes Profit After Years Of Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania Breweries
Limited (TBL) has declared its first dividend of 7 million US
Dollars for 1995 for its joint venture partners after making
losses for more than 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Speaking before President Benjamin Mkapa's speech to mark the
official inauguration of Mwanza Brewery in Mwanza over the
weekend, TBL Board of Directors Chairman Mr Paul Bomani said the
company's 1995 performance signals return to profitability.
</P>
<P>
TBL is a business partner with the South African Breweries
(SAB) through its subsidiary, Indol.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture was concluded in November 1993 and building of
the Mwanza Brewery started in January 1994.
</P>
<P>
Mr Bomani said that declaration of the dividend was a result
of the joint venture's 1995 profit of 14 million US Dollars after
substantial rehabilitation had been made at the Dar es Salaam
Brewery.
</P>
<P>
The Mwanza Brewery is located at Pasiansi, a few kilometers
from Mwanza town, on the shores of Lake Victoria. Since starting
production, it has produced over 260,000 crates of beer.
</P>
<P>
After improving production level by 12 percent in 1994, up
from the 1993 level, performance during 1995 showed an increase
of 83 percent despite power and water supply problems. This is 61
percent rise on the 1994 production level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
