<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 11:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Expects Separation with Palestinians Within 2 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Internal Security
Minister Moshe Shahal said today that he expects the plan of
separation between Israel and the Palestinian areas to be
completed within one to two years.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli government decided to implement the separation
plan especially following the recent wave of Hamas suicide
bombing attacks in Israel, which killed 58 people within nine
days.
</P>
<P>
Speaking during a tour to the coastal area between Israel
and the Gaza Strip, Shahal also said he has decided that
checkpoints at the sea-line between Israel and the Palestinian
areas will be jointly operated by both sides.
</P>
<P>
His decision thus reversed earlier recommendation by Israeli
security officials to have separate posts.
</P>
<P>
Shahal added that the close international cooperation against
terrorism has made it possible for the Israeli police to
investigate into two Hamas-affiliated Islamic institutions, which
were recently closed down in Nazareth and east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Israeli security sources said today that since the
closure on the Gaza Strip and the West Bank was eased this
week, 500 tons of flour, rice and milk have entered the
Strip from Israel via the Karni crossing point.
</P>
<P>
Israel has also allowed shipment of some 640 tons of flour to
enter Gaza from Egypt via Rafah.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that there is no shortage of food in Gaza and
that the Palestinians have not submitted any request for more
food supplies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
