<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Communist Party Leader Met with Cambodian Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Communist Party leader
Do Muoi and Norodom Ranariddh, President of the Juncinpec Party
and First Prime Minister of Cambodia, met Sunday in Vientiane, the
capital of Laos, according to Vietnam News Agency (VNA).
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are now in Vientiane attending the Sixth
Congress of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party (LPRP).
</P>
<P>
During their meeting, VNA reported, General Secretary Do Muoi
said that Vietnam, Laos and Cambodia, which all share many
similarities and were invaded by colonialism and imperialism,
should rely on one another and work together for national
reconstruction to get rid of poverty on the basis of mutual
respect for independence and sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese leader expressed thanks to King Norodom Sihanouk
and the Khmer people for their great support and assistance to the
Vietnamese people in their struggle for national independence,
freedom and reunification, VNA said.
</P>
<P>
He also highly appreciated the achievements recorded by the
Cambodian government and people in socio-economic restoration and
development.
</P>
<P>
VNA also said Norodom Ranariddh expressed his satisfaction at
the constant development of Cambodia-Vietnam relations, especially
since the official visit to Cambodia by Vietnamese President Le
Duc Anh in August 1995 and a return visit to Vietnam by King
Norodom Sihanouk in December last year.
</P>
<P>
He further expressed his hope that Cambodia and Vietnam will
boost their bilateral cooperation in all areas, especially in
agriculture and energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
