<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Market Dips </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
closed slightly lower today.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index dipped by 0.2 point to 2,234.6 points
as calmness prevailed in overseas markets during last weekend.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index inched up 0.2 point to 3,334.1
points, while the all resources index dropped 0.4 point to 1,405.1
points.
</P>
<P>
Local dealers said that investors were waiting to see movements
in New York and Tokyo bourses, which provided little direction to
the local bourse. A mostly unchanged Australian dollar also
underpinned the calmness in the Australian stock market.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totalled 219.53 million shares, valued at
632.69 million Australian dollars (487.17 million US dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
