<DOCNO> XIE19960318.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 09:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Exports May Be Affected by EU's New GSP Move </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)'s new
proposal of Generalized System of preference (GSP) on agricultural
products will affect certain categories of Thai exports to the
Western trading bloc when it comes into force this year, a Thai
Commerce Ministry report said today.
</P>
<P>
The new move of EU's GSP was based on a criterion similar to
that of industrial products, which would particularly affect
export of Thai seafood, food products, and decorated flowers, said
the report carried by the Thai News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Under the new GSP proposal, approved by the EU's Commission on
March 6, developing countries with relatively higher development
levels, like Thailand, are more likely to be withdrawn from the
trading privilege in some categories of farm products, especially
those considered sensitive ones.
</P>
<P>
Thailand considers the EU proposal as unfair and discriminatory
in the narcotic policy, and will acceleratedly lobby EU member
countries to change the policy before the proposal's final
approval in late April, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960318.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 09:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE's GDP to Hit 41.53 Billion Dollars in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Gross Domestic Product
(GDP) of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) is expected to reach
41.53 billion U.S. dollars in 1996, against 39.34 billion dollars
(preliminary) in 1995 and 36.88 billion dollars in 1994.
</P>
<P>
An annual report of the Ministry of Planning predicted the
revenues of the non-oil sector to reach 27.6 billion dollars in
1996, as against 26 billion dollars in 1995 and 24.6 billion in
1994.
</P>
<P>
The UAE population in 1996 is expected to rise to 2.5 million
at the end of 1996 compared with 2.2 million in 1994 and 2.3
million in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The UAE's workforce is also expected to rise to one million in
1996, as against 955,000 in 1995 and 913,000 in 1994, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
But per capital national income is expected to drop to
13278.69 dollars in 1996, from 13688.52 dollars in 1995 and
13469.95 dollars in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the UAE is expected to witness economic
stability in 1996, which would be reflected in the performance of
its economic sectors in general.
</P>
<P>
The year will also witness an upsurge in the volume of
investment in various sectors, basically manufacturing, the report
noted.
</P>
<P>
It said the petrochemical industries are assumed to bag the
major share of these investments, including expansion of Ruwais
Refinery, establishment of a new petrochemical complex in
Ruwais, and Al Hamriah Refinery.
</P>
<P>
The stock exchange is expected to be officially opened by
mid-1996.
</P>
<P>
Oil income from the UAE, which produces 2.16 million barrels
per day, bpd, of crude, is also expected to increase due to world
oil demand was projected to increase by 1.6 million bpd in 1996,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
However, the volatility of the U.S. dollar has to be taken into
account, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
