<HEADLINE> Japan To Give Tanzania Grant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Japan will grant Tanzania
more than 4 million US Dollars to help her reinforce the power
distribution network in Kilimanjaro Region, northern Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Japanese Embassy here at the weekend
said the money will be spent on buying transformers and other
equipment for Nyumba ya Mungu Dam in Kilimanjaro Region.
</P>
<P>
The Minister for Finance, Mr Simon Mbilinyi will today sign
exchange notes here on behalf of the Tanzania government, while
acting Japanese ambassador to Tanzania, Mr. Shigeyuki Suzuki will
sign on behalf of his government.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, the project is expected to
increase power supply capacity and improve economic production
activities in Kilimanjaro Region.
</P>
<P>
The grant is part of Japan's increased food production aid (KR
11). Japan has so far granted a total of 9 million US Dollars to
Tanzania under KR 11 scheme for the 1995 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Japan has been providing Tanzania with grants aimed at
increasing production under the scheme since 1978.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ambassador Susuki will today hand over 20,000 tons
of fertilizers to the Deputy Minister for Agriculture, Livestock
Development and Cooperatives, Mr Njelu Kasaka here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
