<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia to Plant More Trees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region in north China, has vowed to plant 330,000 hectares of
trees every year until the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
It will bring newly-planted areas up to 1.3 million ha. in the
coming five years, an official from the regional forestry
department said.
</P>
<P>
The autonomous region's authority is ambitiously pushing
forward reforms of forestry, including leasing barren areas
suitable for afforestation, and combining tree-planting with
farming.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the century, 20 counties are expected to have
all barren areas covered with trees, with an annual output value
of forests reaching two billion yuan (about 240 million US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Inner Mongolia is the largest forest base in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
