<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Irrigation Projects for Ningxia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region,
one of the driest areas in China, is to build ten key water
conservancy projects in the forthcoming five years to help the
development of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The projects will bring an additional of 73,000 hectares of
arid land under irrigation, harness soil erosion on 4,000 sq. km.,
and provide clean drinking water for 400,000 people and 160,000
livestock by the end of this century, said an official with
regional department of water resources.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade, a water conservancy system, which
combines flood control, irrigation with drinking projects, has
taken shape in Ningxia at a cost of two billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The region has built 22 large irrigation zones, eight of which
each occupy 20,000 ha. So far, 80 percent of grain and 90 percent
of vegetables produced in Ningxia have come from the irrigated
zones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
