<HEADLINE> Chengdu to Host International Food Processing and Packaging Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A showcase international
food-processing and packaging exhibition is to be held between
March 25-29 in Chengdu, capital of southwest China's Sichuan
Province.
</P>
<P>
On exhibition will be packaging machinery, materials,
packaging-containers, processing machinery, food machinery,
printing and plastic machines, according to "China Packaging News".
</P>
<P>
The event is expected to help expand the province's packaging
and food markets, and promote economic co-operation among west
China's Yunnan, Guizhou, Gansu, Shaanxi provinces, and the Tibet
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Rich in various resources, Sichuan is an important base for
processing farm and side-line products. It helped generate 47
billion yuan-worth of output value in the province's food industry
in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Now the local food and packaging industries are built to be
pillar sectors in the province, creating increasing demands for
machinery.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will be co-sponsored by the China Packaging and
Food Machinery Corporation, China Food and Packaging Machinery
Association, and two local companies.  
