<HEADLINE> Over 50 Abducted In Northern Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- More than 50 civilians, mainly
youth, were abducted by the Lord's Resistance Army (LRA) rebels
over the weekend in Aaswa County, 18 miles north of Gulu town,
northern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here today, the areas affected
are Palaro, Abaki and Labwor where Patiko Prison is located
around.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the report said, about 100 rebels also looted food#,
livestock and other property from the people in the countryside.
</P>
<P>
LRA was founded in April 1987 by Joseph Kony, a 32-year-old
former catechist in a catholic parish after he fell out with the
catholic church. 
