<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The second Malaysia-
Singapore Defense Forum will be held here Tuesday, Malaysian
Defense Minister Syed Hamid Albar said today.
</P>
<P>
After visiting the Armed Forces Cooperative head office, Syed
Hamid said the ministerial level meeting will focus on issues
relating to the joint military exercises of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Israel has closed down two
suspected Hamas financial bases -- the Holy Land Fund in
Jerusalem and the Islamic Relief Committee in Nazareth -- as part
of the continuing crackdown on the Islamic extremist organization.
</P>
<P>
According to Israeli reports, the Israeli police and army made
the move against the two institutions on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The police confiscated documents from the Holy Land Fund,
which investigators hope will allow them to locate the exact
sources of Hamas funding.
</P>
<P>
VIENTIANE, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Congress of the
ruling Lao People's Revolutionary Party opened today at the
National Assembly Auditorium in the capital.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A seaplane on a sightseeing
tour crashed today shortly after takeoff from Key West, Florida,
killing five people aboard.
</P>
<P>
The Cessna 206 hit the water with its left wing and flipped
over in the sea after making a sharp turn to avoid hitting a
shopping mall.
</P>
<P>
HANOI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- About 35,000 more Vietnamese boat
people in Hong Kong, Japan and southeastern Asian countries will
be repatriated home, official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
VIENNA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Parliamentarians from the European
Union and central and east European countries ended their meeting
here today after discussing the role of parliaments in European
integration and the EU's extension to eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
During their three-day meeting, many representatives demanded
that the parliaments of the EU member countries get involved in
the EU summit to be held in Turin, Italy, on March 29. The summit
will discuss and amend the Maastricht Treaty.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Russian Communist Party leader
Gennady Zyuganov set out his election program Sunday, offering not
to restore the Soviet Union by force, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Outlining his program for running for the presidency, Zyuganov,
51, stressed that he favors the resolutions approved by the State
Duma (the lower house of Parliament) Friday that denounced the
1991 accords that led to the dissolution of the former Soviet
Union. But, he said, this does not mean that "tomorrow someone
will forcibly annex anyone's territory or encroach on anyone's
sovereignty."
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A senior official of the
Hague-based international tribunal proposed today to set up an
office in Bosnian Serb state.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prosecutor of the International War Crimes Tribunal for
the former Yugoslavia Graham Blewitt made the proposal at a
meeting with Serb Prime Minister Rajko Kasagic in Pale, the Serb
stronghold east of Sarajevo, Tanjug news agency said.
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Arab Gulf states today
renewed their call on the international community to continue
pressure on Baghdad until it complies with U.N. resolution 687 on
eliminating all weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
Wrapping up their two-day meeting in Riyadh, Saudi capital, the
foreign ministers of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) states
also warned that Iraq was still producing internationally-banned
biological and chemical weapons, the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
