<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 08:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BBC Reporter Threatened with Death in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Correspondent of the British
Broadcasting Corporation (BBC) Ms Anna Borzello based in Gulu,
northern Uganda has received death threat from the Lord's
Resistance Army (LRA) rebels, reported a local daily today.
</P>
<P>
The rebels have accused her of "biased reporting" of the
insurgency in the Gulu area.
</P>
<P>
The paper "the New Vision" said, the threat was conveyed to
the BBC "Focus On Africa" editor, Robin White on Thursday by the
rebels' Nairobi-based spokesman, Dominic Wanyama.
</P>
<P>
White rang Borzello in Gulu the same day to inform her of the
threat, said the paper, adding that White warned her to take
extra precautions or pull out of the area altogether.
</P>
<P>
A military source in the government army was quoted by the
paper as saying the army have gathered intelligence report that
the rebels plan to take Borzello hostage to draw international
attention to their cause.
</P>
<P>
The paper also quoted Gulu Resident Minister of State Mrs.
Betty Bigombe as saying two rebel co-ordinators in Gulu Town last
week met rebel commander Alex Otti-Lagony. They discussed the
launching of a political wing as "the next step toward winning
the war" and the intensification of propaganda aimed at
influencing public opinion in favor of the lRA rebels.
</P>
<P>
Bigombe said the rebels could have been angered by Borzello's
reports which did not portray them in good light, but she
believed Borzello has been reporting mostly what she saw.
</P>
<P>
She said the Uganda government would try to raise the Wanyama
issue with the Kenya government soon, because she and her
colleagues know he, living in and operating from Nairobi, has
been to Sudan three times in the last two years to meet Kony,
leader of the LRA and the Sudanese authorities.
</P>
<P>
Wanyama hails from Busia and holds the rank of "Captain"
awarded him by Kony who promoted himself to the rank of Major
General. 
</P>
</TEXT>
