<HEADLINE> Rural and Urban Income Narrows in Shanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The gap in annual net incomes
between rural and urban residents in north China's Shanxi Province
is narrowing.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the per capita income of urban
dwellers in the provincial capital of Taiyuan came to 3,263 yuan
last year, 25 percent higher over 1994's figure.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the per capita income of of farmers surged 30
percent to a historical high of 2,927 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The gap in annual income between rural and urban residents has
been reduced from a ratio of one to 2.5 in 1994, to one to 2.4 in
1995.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official attributed the smaller gap to
energetic development of forestry, animal husbandry, and vegetable
production, and the readjustment of rural industrial structures.
</P>
</TEXT>
