<HEADLINE> Guangdong to Stage More Social Insurance Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province is to take bigger steps to improve its social insurance
system.
</P>
<P>
It is to expand the range of social insurances covering pension
systems for government employees, and different insurances for
employees in foreign-funded, privately-run and township
enterprises, while encouraging an integrated social insurance
system in industrialized and urbanized rural areas.
</P>
<P>
In improving the pension system, individual payments for
pension funds will be raised to over five percent of an
individual's total income; pension distributions will be
rationally adjusted between high-income and low-income people; and
an accounting system for base pensions across the province is to
be adopted.
</P>
<P>
A comprehensive unemployment insurance system for all employees
will be pushed forward, with the strengthening of collecting
insurance premiums, and raising the efficiency for calculating and
distributing unemployment relief money.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a social relief fund system, as well as a training
system, will be established for the unemployed.
</P>
<P>
Legislation will introduced for the setting up of an insurance
system for industrial injuries, by raising medical and
compensation standards, and improving the storage and
concentration of insurance funds to deal with unexpected accidents.
</P>
<P>
Various complementary and life insurances will also be
encouraged, while improving the administration of social
insurances and relevant funds, and the development of social
welfare.
</P>
<P>
The province is also making efforts to speed up legislation
covering pension and unemployment insurances.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
