<HEADLINE> Farmers in Zhejiang Use Credit Cards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Farmer Shu Zhenghui could not
believe how quickly she obtained a 40,000 yuan bank loan. It took
less than one minute.
</P>
<P>
The key to the express money service for Shu, of Ningbo, a port
city in east China's Zhejiang Province, was her new credit card.
</P>
<P>
Shu got the yuan loan within a minute, using the credit card
issued by the Ningbo Branch of Agricultural Bank of China. She
used her borrowed wealth to buy a combine harvester.
</P>
<P>
"I couldn't believe how quickly and conveniently I got my
loan,'' said a delighted Shu.
</P>
<P>
To provide loans for farmers in a more convenient way, the
Ningbo Branch of Agricultural Bank of China has issued credit
cards to 1,500 farmers.
</P>
<P>
Famers receive credit cards after they pass credit ratings, and
they can use their cards to buy farming equipments and materials.
</P>
<P>
The branch has already extended 50 million yuan to farmers
through the credit card system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
