<HEADLINE> China Wins Exports for Yun-12 Planes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- China has signed contracts with
17 countries and regions worldwide for the export of 81 Yun-12
series planes it developed independently in 1980s.
</P>
<P>
A report in the "China Aviation News" says that so far 63
Yun-12s have been delivered to customers in countries such as
Laos, Peru, Sri Lanka and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The Yun-12 series planes are designed and manufactured by the
Harbin Aircraft Manufacture Corporation, in accordance with the
airworthiness standards of the Federal Aviation Administration of
the United States.
</P>
<P>
The plane is safe, reliable and easy to maintain. It requires a
short runway and is 20 to 30 percent cheaper than similar aircraft
in the international market.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturer has so far developed variations for passenger
flights and cargo transport, geological surveying, aerial surveys
and ocean environment monitoring.
</P>
<P>
The plane has obtained airworthiness certificates from the
aviation authorities of China, the United kingdom and the United
States, the report says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
