<DOCNO> XIE19960318.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 07:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wu Yi on Three Express Freight Trains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The three express freight trains
supplying Hong Kong and Macao with fresh and frozen foods and
livestock have run more than 36,000 times since the service
started 34 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics say that the total one-way distance has
amounted to 52.47 million kilometres, equal to more than 1,300
around the equator.
</P>
<P>
"It is a great achievement and miracle in China's railway
transport and foreign trade history," said Wu Yi, Minister of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, in an interview with
Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
The three express freight trains, starting from Shanghai,
Zhengzhou and Wuhan, have carried more than 85 million pigs, five
million head of cattle, one million tons of frozen foods, and a
large amount of eggs, fresh fish and vegetables in the past 34
years.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the three express freight train services started
in 1962, with the support of Premier Zhou Enlai, to meet the
demands of the Hong Kong and Macao compatriots for fresh foods.
</P>
<P>
She said that the service has never been interrupted, even in
the years of natural disasters, Culture Revolution period, heavy
railway transport periods, or when the floods, bridge collapses
and landslides happened en route.
</P>
<P>
"This act fully shows the kindred feelings between the Chinese
government and people and the Hong Kong and Macao compatriots, and
it is also very important to maintain the social stability in the
two regions and ensure the economic prosperity there," she pledged.
</P>
<P>
The railway departments now have a large number of special
freight trains for transporting livestock and frozen food, while
also giving priority to the food trains.
</P>
<P>
More than seven thousand people in the mainland are engaged on
the transport service, escorting the goods, and 12 service stops
have been established en route, providing water, ice and a
maintenance service.
</P>
<P>
Some local departments have also set up bases to raise
livestock, while increasing the proportion of fine breed pigs and
cattle in a bid to ensure the quality of the goods shipped to Hong
Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the central government has attached great
importance to the three express freight trains. Chinese leaders Li
Peng, Qiao Shi and Li Lanqing all gave important instructions and
wrote inscriptions on the task, she added.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (Moftec)
has established a special office, responsible for giving
instructions to the whole process of the work, including giving
quotas, organizing the supply of goods, ensuring transport and
market sales.
</P>
<P>
She promised that the Moftec will, as always, cooperate with
the railway departments, and accomplish the supplies to Hong Kong
and Macao in accordance with the principle of "good quality,
proper quantity, balance and promptness".
</P>
<P>
When asked whether the service of the three express freight
trains will change after Hong Kong returns to the motherland in
1997, she said that the service is by no means an expedient
measure, adding that as the return of Hong Kong and Macao is
approaching, the work is sure to be enhanced and further
improved.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
