<HEADLINE> Shanxi to Expand Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province
will take measures to boost its foreign trade sector in the next
15 years, governor of Shanxi Sun Wensheng has stated.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi plans to maintain a faster growth rate in foreign trade
than the national level during the Ninth Five-Year Plan period
(1996-2000), Sun said at a provincial conference on foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The land-locked province is currently maintaining the fastest
growth rate in foreign trade business among 18 provinces and
autonomous regions in central and western parts of China.
</P>
<P>
"We'll take more practical measures to expand imports and
exports," Sun said.
</P>
<P>
More economic departments, as well as local cities and
counties, will be authorized to directly engage in business with
overseas companies.
</P>
<P>
Export volumes of coal, one of the major export commodities of
Shanxi, is expected to be worth 2.3 billion US dollars in the year
2000 if the province sells more coal after accomplishing a
State-planned export quota.
</P>
<P>
The province has chosen 100 well-operated large and
medium-sized State-owned enterprises and 100 township enterprises,
to substantially increase their import and export volumes in the
next few years.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi will also improve the investment environment, by
publishing more preferential policies for foreign investors, and
upgrading road, air and telecommunication facilities, Sun
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
