<HEADLINE> Sichuan Province Sets up First Legal-Aid Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Free judicial services are being
provided for the needy under the first legal-aid system set up in
southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Rongxian County Attorney Legal-Aid Center will assist poor
residents and enterprises facing court cases in taking up
lawsuits, -- free of charge, according to the Provincial Justice
Department.
</P>
<P>
More centers of this kind are to be established across the
province in the near future, officials of the department told
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan is not the first province in China that has set up
legal-aid centers. Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Zhengzhou
established similar centers last year.
</P>
<P>
Seen as way of reforming the attorney's role, and enhancing
their social responsibility, the legal-aid system was launched in
late 1994 by the Ministry of Justice, with the aim of aiding those
unable to pay for legal services to defend themselves against
lawsuits.
</P>
<P>
The Rongxian county center will establish a special legal aid
fund to provide legal remedies for the lawyers involved in such
cases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
