<HEADLINE> Chongqing to have Asia's Largest Hi-tech Amusement Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Work has started on Asia's
largest hi-tech amusement park that will be out of this world when
completed.
</P>
<P>
The 36 million US dollar park, in the major industrial city of
Chongqing, in southwest China's Sichuan province, will be equipped
with state-of-the-art amusement facilities.
</P>
<P>
The "Spaceship" Amusement Park, a joint venture between
Chongqing and a Hong Kong company, covers an area of 33,000 square
meters and involves a total investment of 300 million yuan,
according to a senior official of the Hong Kong company.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project includes the installment of 125
spaceship-liked domed screens imported from the US, which rotate
in every directions, she said, adding that when pictures are shown
on the screens, visitors will feel as though they are wandering in
the space.
</P>
<P>
It will be completed in July this year, she said.
</P>
<P>
Other facilities include a skating rink with artificial ice,
and a 35-lane bowling alley.
</P>
<P>
The whole project is expected to be completed at the end of
this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
