<HEADLINE> Rural Woman with Remarkable handicrafts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Paper butterflies proved to be a
real tonic for Liu Jiying when she was confined to bed for months
with a long illness.
</P>
<P>
Now the 56-years-old rural woman from northeast China's
Liaoning Province has become known for her 1,000-butterfly
paper-cuts. They all have different sizes and designs and it took
Liu Jiying 30 years to cut this large collection of butterflies.
</P>
<P>
Liu, of Youyan Manchurian Autonomous County, fell in love with
paper-cuts 30 years ago when she was ill, and now she can cut a
butterfly in just over 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Her work has been collected by paper-cut fans from a number of
countries and regions such as Japan, Singapore, Hong Kong and
Taiwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
