<HEADLINE> Hainan's Wild Animal Park Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- China has opened its third animal
safari park with a family of 5,000 wild animals.
</P>
<P>
Newly-built Dongshanhu Wild animal Park in Haikou, capital of
Hainan Province, has opened its gates to visitors.
</P>
<P>
It is the third wild animal park in China, with the other two
located in Shanghai and Shenzhen, Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The 153-hectare park, in the south of the city, has 110 species
of 5,000 wild animals, including tigers, lions, bears, monkeys and
crocodiles.
</P>
<P>
The park plans to develop itself into a medical aid and
breeding center special for wild animals. 
