<HEADLINE> Lao People's Revolutionary Party Opens Sixth Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENTIANE, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Congress of the
ruling Lao People's Revolutionary Party opened today at the
National Assembly Auditorium in the capital.
</P>
<P>
About 600 delegates attended the opening session. Among them
were about 50 members of the current Party Central Committee, and
prominent figures and model workers in various fields of national
economic construction and defence.
</P>
<P>
Seated in the front row at the presidium platform were Party
President Khamtay Siphandone, President of the Lao People's
Democratic Republic Nouhak Phomsavan, and President of the
National Assembly Saman Vinhaket.
</P>
<P>
