<DOCNO> XIE19960318.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-03-18 06:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Economy Sees Stable Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- China's economy continued to rise
steadily in the past two months, with industrial production
witnessing a 14.4 percent growth. The country's retail market
enjoyed further prosperity, in a spell that also saw imports leap
by 34 per cent.
</P>
<P>
A report released today by the State Statistics Bureau in
Beijing said that China's industrial output rose 271.8 billion
yuan in value during January and February, but the sales rate
against production descended 1.49 percentage points from the same
period last year to 92.09 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, the report added, China's retail market
realized a total sales volume of 378.2 billion yuan, up 13.4
percent in real terms on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
The report described the catering sector's business as "selling
like hot cakes", with its sales volume increasing 35.2 percent
during the past two months.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, retail sales in both rural and urban areas rose 21.9
percent and 22.3 percent over the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
"Sales of books also picked up substantially in many places,"
said the report, "which means that Chinese people are demanding
more for cultural and educational consumption, while making a
point of improving their material lives."
</P>
<P>
The report said that China invested 47.5 billion yuan on fixed
assets during the past two months, an increase of seven percent on
a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
Investment on real estate rose 28.2 percent,said the report.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that investment on energy, raw materials and
the electronics industries was stepped up, but the ratio of
investment in agriculture compared to China's total investment
decreased.
</P>
<P>
The report said that China exported 17.83 billion US
dollars-worth of goods in the January-February period, a drop of
1.3 percent from the same period last year. In the same period,
China imported 18.27 billion US dollars-worth of goods, a rise of
34.1 percent, incurring a deficit of 440 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the two month period, banks received 38.2 billion yuan less
in deposits than the same period last year, while loans issued by
the banks fell by 16.5 billion yuan. Of the total loans,
short-term loans saw a reduction of 7.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The report said that China's consumer price index and retail
price index rose 9.2 percent and 7.7 percent respectively during
the January-February period, compared to the corresponding period
last year.
</P>
<P>
In February, the consumer price index and the retail price
index rose 9.3 percent and 7.7 percent respectively on an annual
basis, continuing the same growing momentum as in January.
</P>
<P>
Due to influences of the Spring Festival, China's consumer
price index rose 2.3 percent in February over the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Eggs, meat, poultry, aquatic products and vegetables rose in
price by between 3.7 percent and 12.8 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
