<HEADLINE> US May Stop Food Aid for Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's food situation,
already hard hit by production shortfall, may further deteriorate
as the US government has expressed its inability to provide more
food aid to this country, the local press said today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the Bangladeshi embassy in Washington was
recently informed of the US decision to stop its food aid from
October 1995 to September 1997.
</P>
<P>
The government is worried that other donors, including the
World Food Program, may follow suit, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh is estimated to be in want of 1.6 million tons of
rice this year, according to the Food and Agriculture Organization
(FAO).
</P>
<P>
Agricultural experts said the US decision to suspend food aid
would lead to an additional food import by Bangladesh worth about
70 million US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
