<HEADLINE> McManus Wins Thai Open Snooker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Alan McManus, world number six
from Scotland, defeated Ken Doherty of Ireland 9-8 to win the
Thailand Open snooker tournament in the early hours Monday.
</P>
<P>
In a thrilling battle that went the full 17 frames, McManus,
25, defeated Doherty, 26, with scores 62-46, 53-72, 39-63, 78-28,
67-35, 5-115, 63-24, 80-1, 0-87, 0-120 (break 120), 62-51, 71-45,
0-93, 33-68, 0-71, 73-28, 69-54.
</P>
<P>
McManus receives the 40,000 pounds top prize as the champion
plus 5,000 pounds for matching the highest break of 139, while
Doherty receives 22,500 pounds as runner-up.
</P>
<P>
It the seventh win for McManus in a total 11 matches played
against Doherty, the world number nine. 
