<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A seaplane on a sightseeing
tour crashed today shortly after takeoff from Key West, Florida,
killing five people aboard.
</P>
<P>
The Cessna 206 hit the water with its left wing and flipped
over in the sea after making a sharp turn to avoid hitting a
shopping mall.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the plane appeared to lose power after taking
off and was flying low. Black smoke was seen coming from the
engine before the crash.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the Key West said four members of a South Carolina
family and the pilot were killed. But the family's 10-year-old son
survived the crash. He was treated for multiple injuries.
</P>
<P>
The plane was registered to Key West Seaplane Service, which
flies tourists to the nearby Dry Tortugas islands. 
