<HEADLINE> Thai Government Wants Senate to Support Political Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government hopes that
the new Senate to be inaugurated this weekend will back its
planned political reform, a government spokesman was quoted as
saying by local newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Banharn Silpa-Archa, who is solely empowered to
appoint senators under the constitution, is scheduled to unveil
the list of 260 new senators Friday after the current Senate's
term expires Thursday, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
The government wants the new senators to play an important role
in supporting its push for political reform and important pieces
of legislation, said spokesman Somsak Prisnananthakul.
</P>
<P>
Political reform is vital for Thailand's future, said the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Current Senate Speaker Meechai Ruchupan may retain his post,
according to the spokesman.  
</P>
