<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Takes Cricket World Cup Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka won cricket's World
Cup in Lahore, Pakistan on Sunday with a seven wicket win over
Australia in the final.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka won with just under four overs to spare, scoring 245
for three in reply to Australia's 241 for seven off their
allotted 50 overs.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time for Sri Lanka to lift a World Cup laurel.
</P>
<P>
Aravinda De Silva cracked a brilliant unbeaten 107 and Asanka
Gurusinha contributed 65 as Sri Lanka overhauled Australia.
</P>
<P>
The experienced pair put their squad on the victory path with a
125-run stand for the third wicket after openers Sanath
Jayasuriya and Romesh Kaluwitharna were dismissed by the sixth
over.
</P>
<P>
Some 35,000 spectators at the Gaddafi stadium applauded the
jubilant Sri Lankans, who became the first team in history to win
the World Cup by chasing a target. The previous five tournaments
were won by teams batting first. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
