<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-French joint venture is
to be set up in Shanghai, China's largest city, to produce 33,000
tons of hydrogen peroxide solution annually.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Os Chemical Industry Co. Ltd., a joint effort
between the Shanghai Coke-Oven Plant and France's Os Co. Ltd, is
located in Wujing Town, a chemical industrial area in the suburbs
of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The project, the largest and most advanced of its kind in
China, is expected to begin operations in early 1999.
</P>
<P>
Now world's Demand for the hydrogen peroxide solution, a green
chemical product in the 21th century, is soaring in the
paper-making, chemical, and textile industries. 
