<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Chinese Private Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank is expected to
provide the first ten million US dollars in loans to Chinese
private enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The Shenyang Branch of the Bank of Communication of China, one
of the top banks in the country, will arrange the loans for six
private enterprises in Shenyang, capital city of northeast China's
Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises produce air-conditioners and tonic products,
among others, and will use the loans to import equipment and
production lines.
</P>
<P>
In September, 1994, the World Bank approved the first wholly
US-dollar-dominated loans for Chinese industrial projects. The 175
million US dollars worth of loans are targeted at upgrading
industries in Shenyang, and the World Bank demanded that at least
ten million US dollars of the loans benefit private enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank has been a major international financial
institutions supporting China's economic growth in the past few
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
