<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Modahl Sues British Athletic Federation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
London, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Diane Modahl is sueing the British
Athletic Federation for 480,000 pounds (750,000 U.S. dollars)
compensation over her drugs case, the federation's annual meeting
was told in Birmingham this weekend.
</P>
<P>
The figure was disclosed by treasurer John Lister, who said
that 195,000 pounds (300,000 dollars) had already been spent on
the case.
</P>
<P>
Modahl, an 800 meters specialist, was banned for four years by
the federation's disciplinary hearing after testing positive in
Lisbon in 1994, then cleared by an appeals panel.
</P>
<P>
She is claiming for legal and scientific fees and loss of
earnings while suspended.
</P>
<P>
Next weekend, the International Amateur Athletic Federation
will decide whether to accept the panel's verdict or refer the
case to arbitration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
