<HEADLINE> Pioline Wins Copenhagen Tennis Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Third seed Cedric Pioline of
France captured his first career title Sunday, defeating seventh
seed Kenneth Carlsen of Denmark 6-2, 7-6 (9-7) in the finals of
the 203,000 U.S. dollars Copenhagen Open tennis tournament in
Denmark.
</P>
<P>
Pioline, who was ranked 32nd in the world prior to this week,
was playing in his 10th career final round and third of the
season. He lost to Goran Ivanisevic at the Croatian Open on
February 4 and to Guy Forget two weeks later in Marseille.
</P>
<P>
Pioline, who eliminated unseeded Tim Henman of Britain in
Saturday's semifinals, is now 3-1 all-time against Carlsen, who
beat unseeded Johan Van Herck of Belgium Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Carlsen was playing in his first final since 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
