<HEADLINE> Tunisia Wins Atlanta Olympic Soccer Final Berth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Tunisia lost 2-0 to Guinea in
Conakry in an Olympic soccer African zone second leg qualifying
match on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
However, Tunisia qualified for the finals of Atlanta Olympic
Games on a 5-4 aggregate.
</P>
<P>
The Tunisian press agency (TAP) reported, Tunisia trailed 0-1
at the half time.
</P>
<P>
Mohamed Soumah Wandel scored twice for Guinea at the 31st and
65th minute respectively.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia beat Guinea 5-2 in the first leg match played in Tunis
on March 3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
