<HEADLINE> U.S. Congressman Commends Nigerian Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A United States Congressman has
described Nigeria's local government delegate's election as a
remarkable start for the enthronment of an enduring democracy in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Roy Inis, who led a team of U.S. congressmen as observers to
the Nigerian election told the News Agency of Nigeria that the
turn-out was "amazing and impressive", and "We did not envisage
this huge turn-out."
</P>
<P>
Inis condemned the attitude of those Nigerians, who fled the
country and were calling for the boycott of the election from
abroad and urged them to stop the act and join hands with
compatriots at home to establish an enduring democracy for the
country.
</P>
<P>
Inis, who is also Chairman of the U.S.-based congress for
racial equality, noted, the outside world "has been misinformed
about the goings-on in Nigeria, hence the call for sanctions
against the country from several quarters".
</P>
<P>
The U.S.team, which is in Nigeria to observe and monitor the
election, is obliged to inform the U.S. government correctly of
Nigeria's democratisation process.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has been critising Nigeria for jeopardising democracy
and imposing together with a few other western countries
sanctions against Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
"As observers," Inis stated, "We hereby appeal to all persons
involved in the campaign of calumny against Nigeria to visit the
country before reaching conclusions."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
