<HEADLINE> Sudanese President Reiterates Keen Desire to Cooperate with OAU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese President Omar
al-Bashir today reiterated his country's keen desire to cooperate
with the Organization of African Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
General Bashir made this reiteration during his meeting with
visiting OAU Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salim.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, Salim said that his talks with President
Bashir dealt with the developments related to the U.N. Security
Council resolution on the extradition of three persons accused of
involvement in an assassination attempt on Egyptian President
Hosni Mubarak in Addis Ababa last June.
</P>
<P>
Salim added that President Bashir had asserted during the
meeting his country's keen desire to cooperate with the OAU in
this case.
</P>
<P>
Discussing with President Bashir the consequences of the
Security Council resolution, the OAU Secretary General said he had
emphasized the gravity of the situation and the serious nature of
the crisis should Sudan fail to cooperate with the international
community.
</P>
<P>
Salim pointed out that he had also discussed with President
Bashir ways of implementing the Security Council resolution, and
prospects of averting the escalation of the crisis concerning the
suspects case.
</P>
<P>
The OAU official also met in Khartoum Sunday with Sudanese
Foreign Minister Ali Osman Mohammed Taha and Interior Minister
Bakri Hassan Salem to discuss the suspects case.
</P>
<P>
Salim Ahmed Salim left Khartoum this afternoon after concluding
a two-day visit to Sudan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
